## Cancellation policies

Providers choose one policy per service. Three options, seeded in `cancellation_policies` table:

| Policy | Name | Rules |
|---|---|---|
| `flexible` | Fleksibel | Full refund up to 24h before start; no refund after |
| `moderate` | Moderat | Full refund up to 48h before; 50% refund 24–48h before; no refund within 24h |
| `strict` | Streng | No refund once booked |

Rules are stored as a `jsonb` array on `cancellation_policies.rules` and evaluated at cancellation time:
```ts
// lib/bookings/cancellation.ts
export function calculateRefund(
  policy: CancellationPolicy,
  scheduledAt: Date,
  cancelledAt: Date,
  totalAmountOre: number
): number {
  const hoursUntilStart = differenceInHours(scheduledAt, cancelledAt)
  const rule = policy.rules
    .sort((a, b) => b.hours_before - a.hours_before)
    .find(r => hoursUntilStart >= r.hours_before)
  const refundPercent = rule?.refund_percent ?? 0
  return Math.round(totalAmountOre * (refundPercent / 100))
}
```

**Key rules:**
- `bookings.cancellation_policy_id` is always a snapshot of the policy at booking time — never look up the current service policy after booking, the provider may have changed it.
- Stripe refunds are issued via `stripe.refunds.create()` in the cancellation API route.
- If the provider cancels (not the buyer), the buyer always receives a 100% refund regardless of policy.
- Admin can override cancellation policy in dispute resolution.

