## Provider availability

Providers set their availability in two layers:

### 1. Weekly schedule (`availability_slots`)
Recurring availability by day of week. Providers set this in `/dashboard/tilgjengelighet`.

```
Monday:    09:00–17:00
Wednesday: 09:00–17:00
Saturday:  10:00–16:00
```

If a provider has no slots configured, they are treated as available all the time (opt-in scheduling, not opt-out).

### 2. Exceptions (`availability_exceptions`)
Specific date overrides — either full-day blocks or custom hours for a date.

```
2025-06-17: blocked (Constitution Day)
2025-07-15: available 12:00–16:00 (custom hours, overrides weekly)
```

### Booking availability check
Before confirming any booking (instant or quote-accepted), run:

```ts
// lib/availability/check.ts
export async function isProviderAvailable(
  providerId: string,
  scheduledAt: Date,
  durationMinutes: number
): Promise<boolean> {
  const endTime = addMinutes(scheduledAt, durationMinutes)
  const date = format(scheduledAt, 'yyyy-MM-dd')
  const daySlug = format(scheduledAt, 'EEE').toLowerCase() as DayOfWeek

  // 1. Check for full-day block exception
  const exception = await getException(providerId, date)
  if (exception?.is_blocked) return false

  // 2. Check if time falls within available slot (exception hours or weekly)
  const slot = exception ?? await getWeeklySlot(providerId, daySlug)
  if (!slot) return true  // no schedule configured = always available
  if (!isWithinSlot(scheduledAt, endTime, slot)) return false

  // 3. Check for conflicting confirmed bookings
  const conflict = await getConflictingBooking(providerId, scheduledAt, endTime)
  return !conflict
}
```

The UI date/time picker should call a lightweight `/api/availability/check` endpoint to grey out unavailable slots before the buyer tries to book.

