## Notification system

All in-app notifications are rows in the `notifications` table. Supabase Realtime broadcasts new inserts to the authenticated user's client subscription.

### Notification types

| Type | Trigger | Who receives |
|---|---|---|
| `booking_request` | Buyer submits instant book | Seller |
| `booking_confirmed` | Booking confirmed | Buyer |
| `booking_cancelled` | Either party cancels | Both parties |
| `quote_received` | Seller sends quote offer | Buyer |
| `quote_accepted` | Buyer accepts quote | Seller |
| `quote_declined` | Buyer declines quote | Seller |
| `quote_expired` | 48h elapsed, no response | Buyer |
| `review_request` | Booking completed | Both parties |
| `review_posted` | Both reviews revealed | Both parties |
| `message_received` | New message in thread | Recipient |
| `payout_sent` | Stripe payout triggered | Seller |
| `verification_approved` | Admin approves BankID | Seller |
| `dispute_opened` | Buyer/seller opens dispute | Admin + counterparty |

### Creating notifications (always server-side)

```ts
// lib/notifications/send.ts
export async function sendNotification({
  userId,
  type,
  data,
  sendEmail = true,
}: NotificationInput) {
  const supabase = createAdminClient()

  // Insert to DB (Realtime will push to client)
  await supabase.from('notifications').insert({ user_id: userId, type, data })

  // Send email for high-priority types
  if (sendEmail && EMAIL_NOTIFICATION_TYPES.includes(type)) {
    await sendTransactionalEmail({ userId, type, data })
  }
}
```

### Client subscription (Realtime)

```ts
// hooks/useNotifications.ts  ('use client')
export function useNotifications(userId: string) {
  const [notifications, setNotifications] = useState<Notification[]>([])

  useEffect(() => {
    const channel = supabase
      .channel(`notifications:${userId}`)
      .on('postgres_changes', {
        event: 'INSERT',
        schema: 'public',
        table: 'notifications',
        filter: `user_id=eq.${userId}`,
      }, (payload) => {
        setNotifications(prev => [payload.new as Notification, ...prev])
      })
      .subscribe()

    return () => { supabase.removeChannel(channel) }
  }, [userId])

  return notifications
}
```

The `<NotificationBell>` in the nav shows an unread count badge and drops down to a list. Mark-as-read sets `notifications.read_at`.

